# UVO Order Assistant

A Chrome extension that automatically monitors and takes new orders on the UVO Corp platform.

## Key Features

- Automatically captures new orders that match your criteria
- Regularly refreshes the page to see new orders
- Configurable settings for refresh interval and time requirements
- Tracks taken orders and provides notifications
- Easy-to-use interface with real-time updates

## Installation

1. Download all the files and place them in a folder
2. Open Chrome and go to `chrome://extensions/`
3. Enable "Developer mode" in the top-right corner
4. Click "Load unpacked" and select the folder containing the extension files
5. The UVO Order Assistant icon should now appear in your browser toolbar

## Files Required

Make sure you have all these files in your extension folder:

- `manifest.json` - Extension configuration file
- `popup.html` - Extension popup interface
- `popup.css` - Styles for the popup
- `popup.js` - JavaScript for the popup
- `content.js` - Content script that runs on UVO Corp pages
- `background.js` - Background script that handles events
- `icons/` folder containing:
  - `icon16.png`
  - `icon32.png`
  - `icon48.png`
  - `icon128.png`
  - `success-svg.png`
  - `error-svg.png`
  - `info-svg.png`
  - `pause-svg.png`
  - `spinner-svg.png`
  - `warning-svg.png`

## How to Use

1. Navigate to the UVO Corp orders page (`uvocorp.com/orders/available.html`)
2. Click the UVO Order Assistant icon in your browser toolbar
3. Use the toggle switch at the top to start/stop the bot
4. Configure the settings as needed:
   - **Check Interval**: How often the bot scans the current page (in seconds)
   - **Page Refresh**: How often the page is refreshed to see new orders (in seconds)
   - **Min. Time Remaining**: Minimum deadline time required for orders (in hours)
   - **Sound Alert**: Enable/disable sound notifications for new orders
   - **Auto-pause**: Automatically pause when leaving the orders page

5. Use the "Refresh Now" button to manually refresh the page if needed
6. The activity log at the bottom shows a history of the bot's actions

## Important Notes

- The bot will only process orders marked as "new" on the UVO Corp platform
- Orders must have at least the specified minimum time remaining to be processed
- The bot automatically pauses when you navigate away from the orders page
- You can see how many orders have been taken in the stats section
- When the bot is running, a small spinner will appear in the bottom-left corner of the page

## Troubleshooting

- If the bot isn't working, make sure you're on the correct UVO Corp orders page
- Try refreshing the page manually if you don't see any new orders
- If the extension isn't responding, try reloading it from the Chrome extensions page
- Check the activity log for any error messages
- Make sure your Chrome is up to date

## Privacy & Security

- This extension only operates on the UVO Corp website
- All data is stored locally in your browser
- No data is sent to external servers
- The extension only needs permissions to access and modify UVO Corp pages

## Support

If you encounter issues or have suggestions for improvements, please contact the developer.